# Goals

---

## Editor-G1 AutoDown Editor Foundation
**Status:** proposed
**Module:** editor
**Tags:** stack:frontend, module:editor
**Depends on:** none

- [ ] AutoDown editor provides WYSIWYG block-based editing experience
- [ ] Editor supports Markdown and AutoDown format serialization
- [ ] Block-based architecture enables rich content editing

## Editor-G2 Phase 1 - Markdown WYSIWYG
**Status:** proposed
**Module:** editor
**Tags:** stack:frontend, module:editor
**Depends on:** Editor-G1

- [ ] Implement basic Markdown WYSIWYG editing capabilities
- [ ] Support common Markdown formatting (bold, italic, headings, lists)
- [ ] Provide real-time preview and editing modes

## Editor-G3 Phase 2 - AutoDown Extensions
**Status:** proposed
**Module:** editor
**Tags:** stack:frontend, module:editor
**Depends on:** Editor-G2

- [ ] Add AutoDown-specific block types and components
- [ ] Support custom block attributes and metadata
- [ ] Enable AutoDown serialization and deserialization

## Editor-G4 Phase 3 - Advanced Editing Features
**Status:** proposed
**Module:** editor
**Tags:** stack:frontend, module:editor
**Depends on:** Editor-G3

- [ ] Implement collaborative editing features
- [ ] Add advanced formatting and styling options
- [ ] Provide keyboard shortcuts and accessibility improvements
